flowRoot.flowPara: Supplementary Figure 3. spacemake offers a built-in novosparc integration, either with de-novo reconstruction, or with mapping a single-cell dataset onto a spatial locations. (A) Zeisel et. al adult mouse brain data (Tissue labels used: Thal, CA1, Hypoth, Ctx2, DentGyr, SScortex; n-cells=30k) onto an in-silico created circular puck with 5000 locations. (B) After novosparc-mapping, 80% of the spots in the dataset will have more genes expressed. (C) Expression of spatially-informative genes (identified using squidpy, with the Moran I autocorrelation method) - original dataset vs zeisel mapped with novosparc. (D) Novosparc expression patterns of spatially informative genes. Mean values of the bimodal distributions are plotted for each gene. To arrive at the conclusion from panel (B), each genes expression after novosparc mapping was modeled with a Gaussian Mixture model with 2 components. For each spot, only genes whose expression was in the upper 'peak' were counted..
